	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Conakry - Five young children were killed in an arson attack on Tuesday during clashes in central Guinea following weekend local elections, a government minister minister said. Huts and houses were set on fire, and "five Guinean infants died in the flames", the minister Boureima Conde said on television on Tuesday, without specifying their age or identity. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  